commit.message:
Prepare to support AccessPointDiagnostic interface

Prepare to support iwd's AccessPointDiagnostic interface, by renaming
the StationDiagnostic type to Diagnostic and by removing all references
to station-mode from the diagnostics window. The AP-mode "Diagnostics"
button has not yet been added, because the AP-mode GetDiagnostics method
currently seems to return an empty dictionary.

Add `show-hidden-networks` config file option

Add a config file option to specify whether or not to show hidden
networks in the list of available networks. Document the option and set
its default value to false.

Respect Meson's libdir option

Respect Meson's `libdir` option in the installation path for the systemd
unit.

Refactor agent.c

Refactor agent.c and fix a maybe-uninitialized warning.

Use buildtype=release by default

Set `buildtype=release` as a default Meson option, to enable
optimization and disable debugging symbols. For debugging,
`buildtype=debug` must now be explicitly set in Meson.
Bump version to 0.9 and update CHANGELOG

Update copyright notice for 2023

Update the copyright notice in README.md and in all source files.

Station diagnostics: Fix rare segfault

It's possible that the diagnostics window could be closed before the
GetDiagnostics dbus call returns, which would result in a segfault.
Avoid this by creating the window after GetDiagnostics returns.

Avoid unnecessary string copies

Use the "&" modifier in GVariant format strings passed to
g_variant_get() and g_variant_iter_next(), to avoid unnecessary string
copies. This fixes a few more memory leaks. SNIScrollHandler now takes
an enum rather than a string scroll orientation parameter.

Refactor sni.c and fix memory leak

Fix a memory leak in sni.c due to a floating GVariant created in
sni_status_set().

Fix memory leak due to network table

When a Station object is destroyed, free all of its networks.

Refactor station_set()

Refactor station_set() to reduce the scope of scanning_var.

Use DeviceProvisioning API properties

Use the DeviceProvisioning API properties that are available as of iwd
1.29, which allow the DPP status and QR code to be recovered if iwgtk is
stopped and restarted. Bump the iwd version requirement to >=1.29.

Fix memory leaks

Fix a few memory leaks due to unfreed strings created by
g_variant_iter_next() and g_variant_get().

Gracefully handle "access denied" DBus error

When an "access denied" DBus error occurs (almost certainly due to the
user's lack of membership in either the netdev or wheel group), exit
gracefully and print a more informative error message.
Add lgbaldoni to contributor list

commit.message: Bump version to 0.8 and update CHANGELOG

Fix memory leak

Free the GskRenderNode which is created when fetching an indicator icon
pixmap.

Set minimum window size

Set the minimum permissible window size to 440x300. This is sufficiently large
to display the device table and three available networks.

Add options for window width and height

Add window width and height options to the config file, and document them in the
iwgtk(5) man page. Also, the theme.dark option has been moved to window.dark.

Update copyright headers

Mention contributors in copyright headers.

Increase device table width

Increase the device table width to 400px to prevent widgets from moving when the
device power is toggled.

Remove comment regarding WEP network type

iwd's documentation has been updated to mention the "wep" network type.

Add empty LINGUAS file

The LINGUAS file is empty for now, but if it doesn't exist, Meson issues a
warning.

Mark UI strings for translation

All strings shown in the UI and via notifications have been marked for
translation. Error messages printed to stderr have not been marked. Some
messages have been modified for clarity, consistency, and translatability.

Initialize gettext in main()

Initialize gettext in main(). Prepare meson.build to generate the .pot, .po, and
.mo files.

Fix compiler warnings

Meson's default warning_level=1 setting enables -Wall, which resulted in several
compiler warnings showing up during the build. These warnings have been fixed.
